<task id="022" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-A-14 Dynamic Playbook List in `invoke_playbook` Tool Description at Chat-Agent Build Time (Pillar 3)</title>
    <phase>Phase A — Data-driven Foundation</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>021</dependencies>
    <blocks>023</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, ai, chat</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies chat-agent build path; dynamic description generation; tenant + capability filtering; tags `bff-api`+`ai`+`chat`.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Independent file modification; gates 023.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    At chat-agent build time, dynamically populate the `invoke_playbook` tool's description
    with the list of playbooks accessible to the calling tenant (filtered by tenant scope +
    capability gates). The description includes each playbook's name + short description,
    so the LLM can decide which `playbookId` to pass.

    Critical-path context: this turns the generic `invoke_playbook` tool from "the LLM
    must know the IDs" into "the LLM sees the menu of available playbooks at request time."
    Task 023 (specialized bridge removal) becomes safe ONLY after this lands — without
    dynamic discovery, the LLM wouldn't know which playbookId to pass for, e.g., a
    summarize request.

    Implementation: extend `SprkChatAgentFactory.ResolveTools()` (task 011) to, after
    constructing the `invoke_playbook` AIFunction, mutate or rebuild its description
    string with the dynamic playbook list. Description budget: respect NFR-10 8K system
    prompt budget — if list is long, page or summarize. Cache the description per
    `tenantId` (ADR-014) to avoid re-fetching playbook list on every chat request.

    ADR-015: telemetry from description generation emits playbook-count + tenantId + timestamp
    only; no playbook content / names logged.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer with chat-agent factory build-path expertise and NFR-10 token
    budget awareness.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `invoke_playbook` tool's description string is populated dynamically with the tenant's
    accessible playbooks at chat-agent build time. List respects token budget per NFR-10.
    Cache keyed by `tenantId` per ADR-014. Unit tests cover: empty list (no playbooks) →
    description states "no playbooks available"; long list → paged / truncated within
    budget; tenant isolation. Build green; publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="factory">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
    <file purpose="handler">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Handlers/InvokePlaybookHandler.cs</file>
    <file purpose="bff-claude">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">No new top-level Program.cs lines.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Description generation uses the same facade path; no AI-internal exposure.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Cache key includes `tenantId` per ADR-014.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Telemetry emits playbook-count + tenantId + timestamp; no playbook content logged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Verify BFF publish-size delta; ≤+5 MB R6 budget.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-10">8K system prompt budget preserved; tool description must fit within budget allocation.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-14">SYS-/CUST- enforcement; only tenant-visible playbooks appear in description.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-23">Description includes name + description of each accessible playbook; filtered by tenant + capability gates.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>bff-api/chat-agent-build</topic>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/service-registration.md</file>
